I'm hearing investors worry about inflation as a result of major coronavirus spending, and potentially higher rates and other forms of contractive monetary and fiscal policy, had I been a beginner in investing, this would frighten me. However the market has time and time again proven me again, and it is so tough to predict, which leads me to think it is self correcting, I also think the economy is relatively self correcting meaning the current doom and gloom may cause people to act differently in the markets and economy expecting inflation however it probably wont materialize and when people realize there's nothing to worry about the market takes off. I'm guessing at worst we will have a small decline with major upside, I'm not really changing anything in my portfolio, im holding a couple decent companies that do well and trade options with a small amount just to keep my trading instinct at bay, at the end of the day I believe the market is a game of "see what can not be seen" and that stocks rise pretty high despite crappy fundamentals, or fundamentals can be good despite a low price, eventually there is a reversion to the mean but who knows when.

&#x200B;

However I am still slave to the instinct of trying to predict the market, so I want to leave this post here for me, I am very bullish on stocks, and expect a hell of a market soon, it would be nice to hear others thoughts.
